Direct Formula 1 / Live free practice: Hamilton the fastest in FP2 (Gp USA 2019)
Direct Formula 1 live free practice Gp Usa 2019 Austin: best time for Max Verstappen in FP1, at 9.00 pm Italian FP2 will start (today Friday 1 November).
01 Nov 2019, 21:29 by Mauro Mantegazza
Lewis Hamilton at the top in the second free practice for the United States Grand Prix, the third to last round of the 2019 Formula 1 World Championship. The Mercedes champion was the fastest in the qualifying simulation in 1'33 "232 and also in the race step simulation has shown that it has a rhythm that no one else has been able to replicate. Not even the Ferrari drivers Leclerc (1’33 ″ 533) and Vettel (1’33 ″ 890), in the grip of the Ferraris we find Verstappen (1’33 ″ 547) with Red Bull that offered very positive responses in the long runs. The red tire is perfect to look for the pole position but we will hardly see it used in the race if not in the first few laps, the yellow and above all the white one could become the option for those who want to make a single stop without worrying too much about the degradation of the tires. A positive Friday for Giovinazzi who closed FP2 in tenth position, trimming over half a second to Raikkonen who brought the Rossa to triumph a year ago. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE USA GP TESTS: VETTEL AND LECLERC OK ON THE RACE
Ferrari slightly better than the Mercedes in the simulation of the race pace with red rubber. Leclerc and Vettel run under the 1'40 "unlike Hamilton which instead is a few tenths slower for the same compound, Bottas is instead trying the yellow tire that could work better in the long runs, even the Finn of the Mercedes runs on the 1'40 "low. Red Bull is still working on the dry lap with Verstappen who moved up to third place three tenths from the almost six-time world champion of Formula 1. Even today the big names occupy the first six places of the ranking, Gasly the first of the others with the time of 1'34 ″ 509, in the top 10 we also find Giovinazzi who seems to be particularly at ease on the Austin track, where the second free practice session of the United States Grand Prix is still underway. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE USA GP TESTS: THE SIMIGAN BIG QUALIFICATION
At this time on the Austin track the riders are busy with the qualifying lap simulation. With the red tire Sebastian Vettel scored a 1’33 ″ 890, Charles Leclerc trimmed him three tenths despite using a harder compound, really a great time for the Ferrari driver from Monaco. Even better was Lewis Hamilton who raised the bar in 1'33 "232, the three of them were the only ones to go under the 1'34", only the fourth Bottas that precedes Gasly, Verstappen, Giovinazzi, Kvyat, Hulkenberg and Albon. The Briton of Mercedes is in great shape, on Sunday he will only have to get eighth to confirm himself as Formula 1 world champion for his sixth career but he has no intention of settling for a placement and wants to make it clear since Friday. Missing 45 minutes at the end of the second session of free practice for the US Grand Prix, from here on the teams will concentrate on the race pace. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE USA GP TESTS: GROSJEAN A MURO
Using the yellow rubber, Charles Leclerc set the fastest time so far in 1'34 "742, moving Valtteri Bottas' Mercedes by almost four tenths, third Albon ahead of Grosjean who lost control of his Haas - also because of the many bumps that have come to form on the Austin track and that literally make the cars that pass at full speed jump - ending up on the wall. No problem for the French driver as the car suffered damage to the wing and left front suspension. The commissioners expose the red flag thus interrupting the second session of free practice for the US Grand Prix, the third to last round of the 2019 Formula 1 World Championship. Hamilton, Verstappen and Vettel have not yet entered the standings as they have not been able to complete the lap due to the Grosjean incident. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE USA GP TESTS: WAY TO FP2!
Formula 1 drivers will be back in action soon to compete in the second free practice session for the US Grand Prix, the third to last round of the 2019 World Championship. Compared to a few hours ago, temperatures have risen a few degrees but from here to saying it does hot it takes. Certainly in the 90 minutes of FP2 the teams will focus on the simulation of the qualifying scheduled for tomorrow and on that of the race pace for Sunday, with the aim of understanding which will be the compound that will work best based on certain conditions and consequently the strategy best to adopt. We'll see if the Mercedes continues to hide or if Hamilton and Bottas get back on their feet, after being the fastest in FP1 Verstappen and Red Bull are called to confirm themselves. Hoping that Ferrari will emerge from the big fight ... {adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, USA GP: THE 18-INCH RUBBERS COMES COMING
Let's go back to talking about the revolution that FIA and Liberty Media will put in place from 2021, when Formula 1 enters a new era with an eye to containing costs, leveling forces on the track and increasing the show so as not to sleeping people watching the grand prix after Sunday lunch at grandmother's house - who has the habit of making large portions even for an ox. Among the great innovations announced, the introduction of 18-inch tires (today they have a diameter of 13 inches), a solution that Pirelli has been offering for years and which it had already tried in some private tests. These tires are characterized by a lower shoulder and will be much heavier than the current ones, the different behavior will force the engineers to have to adapt the new machines that will have to respect the constraints and the standards imposed by the Federation. Furthermore, some components will be the same for everyone, in order not to increase the costs that for the top teams reach mind-boggling figures, in the case of Mercedes, Ferrari and Red Bull they even touch the 500 million euro per year. In the face of the economic crisis. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE USA GP TESTS: BEST TIME FOR VERSTAPPEN IN FP1
In the last minutes of the FP1 no one managed to improve the time of Max Verstappen (1'34 ″ 057), the Dutch driver was thus the fastest in the first free practice session of the US Grand Prix that has just ended on Austin circuit. Sebastian Vettel is in the grip of the Red Bulls, the German has turned in 1'34 "226 putting himself in front of Albon (1'34" 316), followed by Gasly (1'35 "008), Ricciardo (1'35" 263) , Grosjean (1'35 "356), Leclerc (1'35" 380) and Hamilton (1'35 "439). Mercedes who worked mainly on the race pace saving the red tire that probably the House of Stuttgart will use in FP2 to simulate the qualification with higher temperatures than those that are now (below 20 degrees). Stroll (1'35 ″ 586) and Magnussen (1'35 ″ 659) with a Haas that appears to be descending after a period of profound technical crisis. Kvyat (1'35 "661), Sainz (1'35" 723), Raikkonen (1'35 "854), Perez (1'35" 971), Giovinazzi (1'36 "037), Hulkenberg (1'36 "124), Bottas (1'36" 159), Norris (1'36 "263), Kubica (1'37" 948) and Latifi (1'41 "112) complete the ranking. The third driver of the Williams turned very little, a pity for the Canadian who wanted to take advantage of this weekend to accumulate more kilometers and gain more and more experience in view of a probable starting promotion for next year. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FREE TEST US GP: VETTEL IN THE BITE OF RED BULL
Only fifteen minutes to go until the end of the first free practice session for the US Grand Prix on the Austin circuit, the Formula 1 drivers set aside the prototype tire that Pirelli will approve next year to focus mainly on the preparation of the qualifying dry lap ( remember that tomorrow the nineteenth pole position of 2019 is up for grabs). With the red tire the fastest was Max Verstappen who drove in 1'34 ″ 057, behind the Dutch we find Vettel's Ferrari (1'34 ″ 226) and the other Red Bull of Albon (1'34 "316). Toro Rosso was very good with Gasly's fourth fastest time (1’35 ″ 008) and the eighth of Kvyat (1’35 ″ 661), Ricciardo's Renault (1’35 ″ 263) fifth ahead of Leclerc. The Mercedes with Bottas and Hamilton in the rear is missing the appeal, the House of Stuttgart is hiding and saves the components in view of the next sessions. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
FORMULA 1, LIVE FREE PROJECTS US GP: THE RED BULLS GIVE THE STEP
On-track activity increased in Austin, where there are about 45 minutes to go until the first free practice session for the US Grand Prix, the third to be held in the 2019 Formula 1 World Championship. With the 2020 tires, Alexander Albon made the best time in 1'35 "282, ahead of his boxmate Max Verstappen by almost three tenths. Both Red Bull riders had to raise because the previous times were canceled because they did not respect the limits of the track. Third position for Sebastian Vettel's Ferrari, in the upper part of the ranking we also find the Stroll and Perez Racing Points, Charles Leclerc is missing (the problem to the power unit seems to have returned, the mechanics promptly fixed the accelerator pedal ) and the Mercedes of Hamilton and Bottas that are running with so much petrol on board and are not interested in finding the perfect lap on Friday morning. More than one pilot complained of the uneven ground with the machines that jump dangerously when they reach 300 kilometers per hour. {Adj. by Stefano Belli}
DIRECT FORMULA 1, FP1 GP USA: MOTOR PROBLEM FOR LECLERC
